cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper addresses the problem of object recognition in image sequences, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed solution involves using a shallow convolutional neural network for classification, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of prior knowledge in object detection and tracking, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper applies the proposed approach to a benchmark data set, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM).
